alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/goN9e7s.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>1. Jacky Hunt-Broersma, a cancer survivor and amputee, sets world record by running 102 marathons in 102 days - She has documented all of her runs (and more) on her Instagram! It's @ncrunnerjacky</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/3QKt4cq.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>2. Black cat known for huge eyes, wonky feet to become mayor of Hell, Michigan. - Jinx the cat to become mayor of Hell, Michigan. This little black cat will rule over Hell, located about 20 miles northwest of Ann Arbor.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/O7w39mx.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>3. LeVar Burton, the beloved former Reading Rainbow host, will receive a Lifetime Achievement Award at the inaugural Children's and Family Emmys in December, the National Academy of Television Arts and Sciences announced this week.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ZDb4ME9.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>4. Plastic-eating Enzyme Could Eliminate Billions of Tons of Landfill Waste - An enzyme variant created by engineers and scientists at The University of Texas at Austin can break down environment-throttling plastics that typically take centuries to degrade in just a matter of hours to days. This discovery was published yesterday in Nature</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/eU6RCrF.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>5. US Army replaces cake it stole from Italian girl in 1945 - Meri Mion - who turns 90 on Friday - was 13 when her village of San Pietro, near Vicenza, saw fighting between US troops and German soldiers. Americans. Sgt Peter Wallis, who handed over the dessert, said it was "a little awkward" to replace the stolen goods, "but it makes me feel great".</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/eeWZbFM.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>6. NAU to provide tuition-free college education for Arizona residents with household incomes at or below $65,000</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/HBDyfjx.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>7. EU reveals plans for the 'largest ever ban' on toxic chemicals - Thousands of potentially toxic or harmful chemicals still used in cosmetics, toys and even baby products could soon be banned in Europe under new regulations.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Gnk2FQy.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>That's it for this week :) Until next week, you can read my previous posts and subscribe here https://feelgoodnews.substack.com/ for a weekly collection of inspirational, feel good news stories from around the globe.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/gXBtWbh</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[FeelGoodNews]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Fork, yeah!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/XCGrL9j</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/RiBueu3.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/XCGrL9j</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[PiercedViking]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Some drawings I made in April</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/3iym6CF</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/hbxSbE1.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/0or1vxW.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/BHkaDAT.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/3ksZkWM.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div